# Get density of points in 2 dimensions.
# @param x A numeric vector.
# @param y A numeric vector.
# @param n Create a square n by n grid to compute density.
# @return The density within each square.
get_density <- function(x, y, ...) {
  dens <- MASS::kde2d(x, y, ...)
  ix <- findInterval(x, dens$x)
  iy <- findInterval(y, dens$y)
  ii <- cbind(ix, iy)
  return(dens$z[ii])
}

set.seed(1)
dat <- data.frame(

  )

Where did these annotated reads come from? These are sscs reads from dunovo there were 6 samples that we ran for our iL3 independence screens for rp4 and rp5, we had d2 and d4 data for the low medium and high concentrations. I merged .fq files for all doses at all time points for rp4 and rp5. That’s 6 for rp4 and 6 for rp5 merged fqs> dunovo make barcodes > dunovo align families > dunovo make families > trimmomatic to filter out Ns > bwa-mem 2 to align to the ABL1 CDS > nvc to call variants > variant annotator to count variants and make the .mut files

raw fastq files

###################RP4###################
rp4_raw=read.table("rp4_annotated.tabular",header = T,stringsAsFactors = F)
colnames(rp4_raw)=c("sample",
                    "chr",
                    "pos",
                    "A",
                    "C",

                    "cvrg",
                    "alleles",

rp4_raw$pos=as.numeric(rp4_raw$pos)
rp4_concat=rp4_raw%>%dplyr::select(pos,A,C,G,T,ref=major,cvrg)
rp4_melt=melt(rp4_concat,
              id.vars=c("pos","cvrg","ref"),
              measure.vars=c("A","C","G","T"),
              value.name = "ct",
              variable.name = "alt"
              )
rp4_melt=rp4_melt%>%filter(!ref==alt)
